main event: A UFO sighting was reported at NAS Key West, Florida on 3rd December 1956 by a civilian observer. The object was described as a bright flash of white light, and its size and distance were unknown. The observation lasted for a few seconds, and the azimuth was 90 degrees from Key West NAS.
interesting points: The UFO sighting was categorized as a Ground-Visual observation.
The object was only observed for a few seconds, making it a brief sighting.
The report indicates that there was insufficient data to make a conclusive assessment of the observation.
The observer was unable to determine the size or distance of the object, adding to the mystery of the sighting.
Various military divisions and agencies were notified and checked for any related missions or activities, but all reported negative.
sighted object: One bright flash of white light
photographs: No photographs were included in the report
